Class ArtistNames

  • Object
    • ArtistNames

  • public class ArtistNames
extends Object
    Class that represents artist names, including the original display name, the normalized name (used internally), and a list of alternate names.
    Author:
    Jon

      • normalizeName

        public String normalizeName()
        Normalizes the artist name. This involves:
        • removing leading "the", including immediately after an ampersand
        • changing "and" to ampersand
        • normalizing various strings that mean "featuring"
        • ensuring that an ampersand is surrounded by whitespace

        The resulting normalized name is much more useful in detecting alternate names.

        Returns:
        normalized name

      • matchArtist

        public int matchArtist(ArrayList<ArtistCorrelator> artistCorrs,
                       Logger artistLogger)
        Matches the artist name against the current list of such names. This includes alternate name detection.
        Parameters:
        artistCorrs - list of current artist name correlators
        artistLogger - logger to use
        Returns:
        zero or a positive index to indicate the index of the found name, or a negative index to indicate the negation of the index at which the artist would be inserted if found

      • checkPostProcessType

        public int checkPostProcessType(ArrayList<ArtistCorrelator> artistNames)
        Checks an artist with a post-processing type to see if the primary artist can be located. If so, then this artist becomes an alternate name for the primary.
        Parameters:
        artistNames - list of all artist name correlators
        Returns:
        zero or a positive index to indicate the index of the found name, or a negative index to indicate the negation of the index at which the artist would be inserted if found
